         1. Introduction

         A6 was written to be a cross-assembler to write code for the
         Commodore 64/128 microcomputers.  It was originally distributed
         only as MS-DOS binaries, and eventually I added Linux and Amiga
         distributions.

         Beginning with version 0.4.3, I have decided to release the
         assembler in source format under the GNU public licence.

         Binary distributions for Amiga and MS-DOS will be generated for
         A6, but the Linux binaries will be discontinued;  most Linux
         distributions contain GCC anyway, and this way I am no longer
         confining myself to i386 and kernel versions 2.0 or better.

         The auto-configure scripts that are found with the current
         version of A6 are very restricted in the number of compilers
         that they support.  If necessary, you can contact me and I will
         alter (or help you alter) the auto-configure scripts to support
         a currently unsupported compiler.

         To prevent annoyance, I've created a FAQ, which can be viewed
         at http://www.powerfield.demon.co.uk/a6/faq.htm





































