         10. Development roadmap

         If you're looking for other features in the assembler, here is
         the roadmap of round-about when I think I'll have these
         features ready.  If you want to go and add them yourself,
         please email me your modifications so that I can share them
         with the A6 user community.  Your effort will be credited.

         0.4.4:
             o  Add T64 and Genius compressed hex as output formats.
             o  Finish the new-improved, faster expression parser.

         0.5 series:
             o  Macro support.
             o  Environment variable to specify include paths
             o  .image directive.
             o  Add Intel and Motorola hex as output formats.
             o  Add T64 as an "incbin" format under the name "inct64".

         0.6 series and beyond:
             o  Conditional assembly.
             o  Startup file to specify options for project.
             o  100% Genius compatability.
             o  Genius-style listing.
             o  Genius-style concordance table.
             o  Ability to assemble "compressed" Genius source files.
             o  Support CPU tables loadable from files.


